[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Spectral Tower
	]em
	" (スペクトラルタワー ) is a role-playing game for the PlayStation that was only released in Japan and the first game developed by Idea Factory, creator of various otaku games such as 
	[em 
		"Cross Edge
	]em
	" and the 
	[em 
		"Neptunia
	]em
	" series. You play as an adventurer that's looking for wonders and treasure, and it's said that the Spectral Tower contains both that are beyond any person's imagination. Your objective is to get to the top of that tower and see what the heavens can give you that Earth can't.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The game is infamous for its extremely long length. Each floor in the towers contain procedurally generated floor layouts and monster layouts, and the titular Spectral Tower contains 1000 of these floors. It also has enemies that can destroy items that you're carrying, chests that have to be attacked if your chest opening level is too low, and dozens and dozens of traps. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For this run, 
